\begin_layout Standard
and this makes 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{1}(a)$
\end_inset

 is more like 
\begin_inset Formula $\int_{-0.1}^{-a}dx\frac{0.00001}{x}$
\end_inset

 .
 And the numerical integral in mathematica can not give a divergent result
 even for 
\begin_inset Formula $\int_{-0.1}^{-a}dx\frac{1}{x}$
\end_inset

, which will lost precision when 
\begin_inset Formula $a<10^{-60}$
\end_inset

 and for 
\begin_inset Formula $a>10^{-60}$
\end_inset

, the result of 
\begin_inset Formula $\int_{-0.1}^{-a}dx\frac{1}{x}>-135.853$
\end_inset


\end_layout

